The paper discusses interference alignment, which is a technique used in wireless communication networks to mitigate interference. This topic falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses practical challenges and test bed implementation, which are related to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of multiple antennas, which falls under Multimedia (cs.MM) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
